In addition to saving money (the average family saves over $500 each year), coops help ensure there is always a sitter available when needed, and they build communityâboth for the parents as well as for the children. Coops have been around for many, many years, but the model is not widely used today. There are two reasons for this: 1) they are not well known; and 2) they require a lot of administrative work to manage.
